article.description: Brittainey Raven scored 13 points as Texas (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) beat Missouri 60-41 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Nash's 3-pointer sparks Texas past Missouri
article.linkText: Raven's 13 help Texas take care of Missouri
article.story:
AUSTIN, Texas -- Brittainey Raven scored 13 points as Texas (No. 22 ESPN/USA Today, No. 18 AP) beat Missouri 60-41 on Wednesday night.

Erika Arriaran added nine points in the win. Cokie Reed held down the low post with nine points and five rebounds but injured her right ankle in the final minute of the game and had to be helped off the court by the training staff.

Toy Richbow's back-to-back baskets forced Texas to call a timeout with a slim 36-30 advantage. After the timeout, Kathleen Nash hit a 3-pointer from the right wing giving Texas a 42-32 lead, and the Longhorns (20-9, 9-6 Big 12) built on that lead for the rest of the game.

Shakara Jones and Jessra Johnson both scored 10 points for the Tigers (11-17, 1-14).
